  "title": "The Huntington's Transformative Rebrand by Base Design Ushers in Era of Openness and Discovery",
  "publishedAt": "2026-01-15T16:23:44.930Z",
  "generatedAt": "2026-01-15T16:23:44.930Z",
  "totalSources": 8,
  "sections": [
    {
      "id": "section-0",
      "paragraphs": [
        {
          "id": "para-0-0",
          "content": "The Huntington Library, Art Museum, and Botanical Gardens in San Marino, California, has unveiled its first comprehensive branding initiative in over 100 years, led by Base Design as part of the \"One Huntington\" strategic plan.The rebrand simplifies the institution's name to \"The Huntington\" and introduces a modern \"H\" monogram featuring stylized pillars flanking a central gem-like form, replacing the previous ornate botanical motif.This visual identity unifies the library, art museum, and gardens, positioning The Huntington as a \"hidden gem: One of one. Rooted in California. Framed for a wider world.\"",
          "citations": [
            {
              "primarySource": {
                "id": "source-1",
                "name": "BP&O",
                "url": "https://bpando.org/2026/01/15/the-huntington-museum-branding-by-base-design/",
                "favicon": "https://www.google.com/s2/favicons?domain=bpando.org&sz=32",
                "title": "The Huntington by Base Design"
              },
              "additionalCount": 1,
              "additionalSources": [
                {
                  "id": "source-2",
                  "name": "huntington",
                  "url": "https://www.huntington.org/news/huntington-revitalize-historic-library-building-and-transform-library-and-art-museum",
                  "favicon": "https://www.google.com/s2/favicons?domain=www.huntington.org&sz=32",
                  "title": "The Huntington by Base Design"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "para-0-1",
          "content": "Base Design's work emphasizes openness, integration, and accessibility, supporting a long-term reimagining of spaces, grounds, and collections.The rollout includes new signage, a refreshed website, digital tools, and merchandise to invite visitors to \"Rediscover The Huntington.\"Local reports highlight how these changes enhance visitor experiences and public engagement with the institution's rich collections.",
