                  "favicon": "https://www.google.com/s2/favicons?domain=www.basedesign.com&sz=32",
                  "title": "The Huntington by Base Design"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "section-2",
      "title": "Integration with Library Modernization and Exhibitions",
      "paragraphs": [
        {
          "id": "para-2-0",
          "content": "The rebrand aligns with an 83,000-square-foot renovation of the 1919 Library building into a unified Library/Art Building, led by Robert A.M. Stern Architects, with groundbreaking in spring 2026.This $126.6 million project, nearing fundraising completion at over $100 million committed, expands conservation studios and exhibition spaces while keeping the research library open.Exhibitions like \"the eight directions of the wind\" by Edmund de Waal will span gardens and galleries, exploring idea transmission.",
          "citations": []
        },
        {
          "id": "para-2-1",
          "content": "Additional 2026 programming includes Mercedes Dorame's \"Deliquescence: Sites of Transformation\" and the \"This Land Is …\" initiative for the U.S. 250th anniversary.These efforts foster curiosity and cross-divisional collaboration amid construction.The Huntington anticipates sustained public engagement and dynamic scholarship through these unified transformations.",
          "citations": []
        }
      ]
    }
